news.title: Madurai corporation orders demolition of 571 buildings
news.para: The civic body ordered for an enumeration of such old buildings in the city limits. The enumeration found 99 buildings in zone 1, 148 in zone 2, 104 in zone 3, 220 in zone 4 of the corporation.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body's property tax portal causes anxiety among netizens
news.para: But this is an unnecessary effort for the citizens. I went to the BBMP office and got it rectified and need to check if I can make the payments now. I know multiple people from Mahadevapura who are facing the same issue,” he said.

news.title: Telangana SCDRC orders Emaar to refund buyer's advance with compensation
news.para: One Alphonse Reddy Chintalavheruvu of Madanapalle, Chittoor district in Andhra Pradesh, filed a petition against AP Industrial Infrastructure Corporation Limited (APIIC), Emaar Hills Township Private Limited and Emaar MGF Limited.

news.title: Gurugram: Only plotted areas, not highrises, in private colonies to be taken over
news.para: According to an MCG official, the proposed takeover is only for plotted areas as colonies and group housing societies (highrises) are governed by different norms.

news.title: HC asks Haryana, Punjab & UT if state-developed projects can be under RERA
news.para: ​HC has passed these orders while observing that several cases being filed by the people from these states conveyed their grouse against the non-fulfilment of promises made by the state agencies in developing various housing projects.

news.title: Noida: Tentative date for Supertech twin towers demolition moved to Aug 21
news.para: The Supreme Court had earlier permitted extending the demolition date till August 28 from May 22 this year after the private company engaged for the work approached it with a plea for time extension.

news.title: AMD leases five lakh sq ft space in Prestige Technostar in Bengaluru
news.para: AMD will use the new office space to expand its operations in the city. The office is expected to be operational by the end of this year. The company signed a 10-year lease in May.

news.title: Real estate demand leads Gujarat government to revise planning rules
news.para: A key source privy to the development said, “There is much ambiguity in policies relating to housing redevelopment, hotels and hospitals and development plans of different cities. All these factors have been hurting real estate development in the state.”

news.title: UP RERA imposes Rs 1.05 crore penalty on nine developers
news.para: The authority found that some of the promoters have indulged in non-compliance of its orders despite the authority granting them sufficient time.

news.title: CBI in UP gets custody of DHFL promoters, court says 'not as per law'
news.para: Last month, lawyers for the Wadhawans moved the court, saying they had been taken to UP from Taloja jail without the court’s permission or a transit remand.

news.title: Take action to keep construction material prices under control: BAI
news.para: The newly elected body of the association made a representation to the minister of state for housing and urban affairs Kaushal Kishore and said that the houses are getting costlier for buyers due to the increase in raw material prices.

news.title: NCLAT orders fresh hearing in Radius Estate insolvency row, sets aside earlier order
news.para: In March, the NCLT Mumbai bench had allowed an application filed by Piramal Capital & Housing Finance Ltd (PCHFL) that had opposed the withdrawal of the insolvency resolution against Mumbai-based real estate developer Radius Estate Projects.

news.title: Telangana: 80 master plans for UDAs, ULBs
news.para: The new master plans will have provision for outer ring roads (ORRs), mixed land use and link roads. Officials said the master plans are necessitated as the government has created 70 new municipalities.

news.title: Soon, portal for complaints against realty fraudsters in Punjab
news.para: Bhagwant Mann gave his nod for launch of a portal to monitor complaints pertaining to plots and apartments where sale deeds have been executed by developers, but possession is still awaited.

news.title: Lease income from 'residential' property is exempt from GST: AAR Maharashtra
news.para: In cities like Mumbai, residential flats are often let out, on a lease and license basis to business entities. In turn, the concerned company allots these flats to its key executives for their residential purposes.
